{
  "stem": "5810.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's 30 minutes already?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As I understand it, all of my family, I don't know where that came from, but I've heard so many times it might have been right, it seemed that everybody was taken to Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yet, I learned later on that Buchenwald was for male Jews-- not-- not female Jews.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I do believe that my brothers were in Buchenwald, and my sister-- sisters-- wound up in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's not confirmed.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I'm still searching today to find out if that's what it was, through the Red Cross.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH], or [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Claudine ?] now.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But yes, my older sister.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we had no home to go to.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we all remember that the underground was very active at that point, trying to save Jews.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we contacted the underground person that had arranged for our escape to Switzerland.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I just-- just remembered something that I needed to tell you, is that at the border, when I told you that they had the names, they knew when, and they knew where.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were denounced.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I later came to find out that it was a member of our family.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But again, for the same reason that I-- I forgive my father for doing what he did to save his life, there were situations in which the Germans had promised any Jews that denounced other Jews would have another year, week, a month, a year, to live.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So this member of our family, because there was a trial later after the war, said as a reason and excuse that she was trying to save her own life.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I've heard tante, which is of course aunt, and that's impossible, because I know that it wasn't any one of my mother or father's brothers or sisters.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
